---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Quantum — Buddy · AIIT-THRESI" description="AIIT-THRESI and quantum mechanics. IBM quantum hardware confirmation. π as boundary geometry. 37 singularities. The edge is real.">

<section style="padding-top: 140px; min-height: 80vh;">
  <div class="container narrow" style="max-width: 820px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 8vw;">
    <div class="eyebrow">The why — quantum</div>
    <h1 style="font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 5rem); margin-bottom: 24px;">Quantum<br>Mechanics.</h1>
    <p style="color: var(--ink-soft); font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.8; max-width: 640px; margin-bottom: 60px;">
      AIIT-THRESI's relationship with quantum mechanics is not metaphorical. IBM quantum hardware confirmed the singularity structure. π is the boundary geometry. The 37 singularities are real Laurent poles — not theoretical constructs.
    </p>

    <div class="q-coming">
      <div class="q-label">IN PREPARATION</div>
      <div class="q-text">This page is being built. The quantum mechanics section of the AIIT-THRESI framework — IBM confirmation, singularity traversal, π winding, the coherence gate structure — will live here.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</Layout>

<style>
  .eyebrow {
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    font-size: 0.72em;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--amber, #D4AF37);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .q-coming {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--amber, #D4AF37);
    padding: 20px 24px;
    background: rgba(212,175,55,0.05);
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
  .q-label {
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    font-size: 0.7em;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    color: var(--amber, #D4AF37);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .q-text {
    font-size: 0.95em;
    color: var(--ink-soft, #999);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }
</style>
